  . Dividing both sides by 
  
    
      
        
          b
          
            1
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle b^{1}}
   gives 
  
    
      
        
          b
          
            −
            1
          
        
        =
        1
        
          /
        
        
          b
          
            1
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle b^{-1}=1/b^{1}}
  , which can be more simply written as 
  
    
      
        
          b
          
            −
            1
          
        
        =
        1
        
          /
        
        b
      
    
    {\displaystyle b^{-1}=1/b}
  , using the result from above that 
  
    
      
        
          b
          
            1
          
        
        =
        b
      
    
    {\displaystyle b^{1}=b}
  . By a similar argument, 
  
    
      
        
