          b
          
            x
          
        
        (
        cos
        ⁡
        (
        y
        ln
        ⁡
        b
        )
        +
        i
        sin
        ⁡
        (
        y
        ln
        ⁡
        b
        )
        )
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle b^{x+iy}=b^{x}(\cos(y\ln b)+i\sin(y\ln b)),}
  where the absolute value of the trigonometric factor is one. This results from

  
    
      
        
          b
          
            x
            +
            i
            y
          
        
        =
        
          b
          
            x
          
        
        
          b
          
            i
            y
          
        
        =
        
          b
          
            x
          
        
        
          e
          
            i
